I have reverted the previous incorrect change. Now I will implement a more robust fix. The issue is that the VPlan cost model (`precomputeCosts`) does not correctly account for the cost of reduction operations when a special, optimized "reduction pattern" is not found. The legacy cost model, in contrast, always costs the individual instructions of the reduction chain. This discrepancy leads to the assertion failure.

My plan is to modify the reduction handling logic within `precomputeCosts` in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp`. I will introduce a fallback mechanism. If the loop that searches for special reduction patterns fails to find one, the code will then iterate through all instructions in the reduction chain (including the PHI node) and sum their individual costs, mimicking the behavior of the legacy cost model. This will ensure both cost models agree.

Specifically, I will:
1.  Introduce a `FoundPattern` boolean flag, initialized to `false`, before checking for reduction patterns.
2.  If a pattern cost is found, set `FoundPattern` to `true`.
3.  After checking for patterns, if `FoundPattern` is still `false`, execute a new block of code that calculates the cost by summing the legacy costs of each instruction in the reduction chain.

This approach is more comprehensive than my previous attempt and should resolve the cost model disagreement. I will use `sed` to insert the necessary code blocks at the appropriate locations in `LoopVectorize.cpp`.

```bash
sed -i '7363 a\    bool FoundPattern = false;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp && \
sed -i '7369 a\      FoundPattern = true;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp && \
cat <<'EOF' | sed -i '7378 r /dev/stdin' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp
    if (!FoundPattern) {
      // If we did not find a pattern cost for any of the instructions in the
      // reduction chain, compute the cost of the reduction using the legacy cost
      // model.
      InstructionCost C = CM.getReductionCost(RedPhi, VF);
      Cost += C;
      LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cost of " << C << " for VF " << VF
                        << ": in-loop reduction " << *RedPhi << "\n");

      // Mark all instructions in the chain as visited.
      for (Instruction *I : ChainOpsAndOperands)
        CostCtx.SkipCostComputation.insert(I);
    }
EOF
```

